Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with information flow and capacity of channels, which are core topics in information theory. 
2. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses closed-loop encoders and feedback systems, which are relevant to the field of systems and control. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with communication systems, which are a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses channels with noisy feedback, which can be relevant to multimedia communication systems. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper introduces a new notion, the residual directed information, which could potentially be relevant to machine learning and data analysis.
